{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":2000,"text":"I'm going to present\nthree projects in rapid fire."},{"time":4405,"text":"I don't have much time to do it."},{"time":6000,"text":"And I want to reinforce three ideas\nwith that rapid-fire presentation."}]},{"cues":[{"time":9358,"text":"The first is what I like to call\na hyper-rational process."},{"time":12358,"text":"It's a process that takes rationality\nalmost to an absurd level,"},{"time":16279,"text":"and it transcends all the baggage"},{"time":18208,"text":"that normally comes\nwith what people would call,"},{"time":20876,"text":"sort of a rational\nconclusion to something."},{"time":23000,"text":"And it concludes in something\nthat you see here,"},{"time":25310,"text":"that you actually wouldn't expect\nas being the result of rationality."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30070,"text":"The second --"},{"time":32790,"text":"the second is that this process\ndoes not have a signature."},{"time":37804,"text":"There is no authorship."},{"time":39204,"text":"Architects are obsessed with authorship."},{"time":41240,"text":"This is something that has\nediting and it has teams,"},{"time":43748,"text":"but in fact, we no longer\nsee within this process,"},{"time":46135,"text":"the traditional master architect"},{"time":47689,"text":"creating a sketch\nthat his minions carry out."}]},{"cues":[{"time":51739,"text":"And the third is that it challenges --"},{"time":53599,"text":"and this is, in the length of this,\nvery hard to support why,"},{"time":57000,"text":"connect all these things --"},{"time":58326,"text":"but it challenges the high modernist\nnotion of flexibility."},{"time":61553,"text":"High modernists said we will create\nsort of singular spaces that are generic,"},{"time":65217,"text":"almost anything can happen within them."},{"time":67130,"text":"I call it sort of \"shotgun flexibility\" --"},{"time":69180,"text":"turn your head this way; shoot;\nand you're bound to kill something."},{"time":72365,"text":"So, this is the promise of high modernism:"},{"time":74464,"text":"within a single space, actually,\nany kind of activity can happen."},{"time":77711,"text":"But as we're seeing,"},{"time":80000,"text":"operational costs are starting\nto dwarf capital costs"},{"time":83000,"text":"in terms of design parameters."},{"time":85063,"text":"And so, with this sort of idea,"},{"time":86807,"text":"what happens is, whatever actually\nis in the building on opening day,"},{"time":90089,"text":"or whatever seems to be\nthe most immediate need,"},{"time":92376,"text":"starts to dwarf the possibility\nand sort of subsume it,"},{"time":95672,"text":"of anything else could ever happen."},{"time":97624,"text":"And so we're proposing\na different kind of flexibility,"},{"time":100245,"text":"something that we call\n\"compartmentalized flexibility.\""},{"time":104403,"text":"And the idea is that you,\nwithin that continuum,"},{"time":106766,"text":"identify a series of points,\nand you design specifically to them."},{"time":109918,"text":"They can be pushed\noff-center a little bit,"},{"time":111959,"text":"but in the end you actually\nstill get as much"},{"time":114096,"text":"of that original spectrum\nas you originally had hoped."},{"time":117000,"text":"With high modernist flexibility,\nthat doesn't really work."}]},{"cues":[{"time":120463,"text":"Now I'm going to talk about --"},{"time":121929,"text":"I'm going to build up\nthe Seattle Central Library"},{"time":124262,"text":"in this way before your eyes\nin about five or six diagrams,"},{"time":127067,"text":"and I truly mean this is the design\nprocess that you'll see."},{"time":129908,"text":"With the library staff\nand the library board,"},{"time":132236,"text":"we settled on two core positions."},{"time":134000,"text":"This is the first one, and this\nis showing, over the last 900 years,"},{"time":137469,"text":"the evolution of the book,\nand other technologies."},{"time":141112,"text":"This diagram was our sort\nof position piece about the book,"},{"time":144000,"text":"and our position was,\nbooks are technology --"},{"time":146540,"text":"that's something people forget --"},{"time":148152,"text":"but it's a form of technology\nthat will have to share its dominance"},{"time":151338,"text":"with any other form of truly potent\ntechnology or media."}]},{"cues":[{"time":155130,"text":"The second premise --"},{"time":156306,"text":"and this was something\nthat was very difficult for us"},{"time":158821,"text":"to convince the librarians of at first --"},{"time":160811,"text":"is that libraries, since the inception\nof Carnegie Library tradition in America,"},{"time":164618,"text":"had a second responsibility,\nand that was for social roles."},{"time":167525,"text":"Ok, now, this I'll come back\nto later, but something --"},{"time":170137,"text":"actually, the librarians at first said,\n\"No, this isn't our mandate."},{"time":173368,"text":"Our mandate is media,\nand particularly the book.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":177463,"text":"So what you're seeing now\nis actually the design of the building."},{"time":180557,"text":"The upper diagram is what we had seen"},{"time":183033,"text":"in a whole host of contemporary libraries\nthat used high modernist flexibility."},{"time":187598,"text":"Sort of, any activity\ncould happen anywhere."},{"time":190679,"text":"We don't know the future of the library;\nwe don't know the future of the book;"},{"time":194405,"text":"and so, we'll use this approach."}]},{"cues":[{"time":196008,"text":"And what we saw were buildings\nthat were very generic, and worse --"},{"time":199212,"text":"not only were they very generic --"},{"time":200934,"text":"so, not only does the reading room\nlook like the copy room"},{"time":203700,"text":"look like the magazine area --"},{"time":205222,"text":"but it meant that whatever issue\nwas troubling the library at that moment"},{"time":208972,"text":"was starting to engulf every other\nactivity that was happening in it."},{"time":212511,"text":"And in this case,\nwhat was getting engulfed"},{"time":214784,"text":"were these social responsibilities\nby the expansion of the book."},{"time":217824,"text":"And so we proposed\nwhat's at the lower diagram."},{"time":220063,"text":"Very dumb approach:\nsimply compartmentalize."},{"time":223174,"text":"Put those things whose evolution\nwe could predict --"},{"time":225651,"text":"and I don't mean that we could say\nwhat would actually happen in the future,"},{"time":229258,"text":"but we have some certainty of the spectrum\nof what would happen in the future --"},{"time":233168,"text":"put those in boxes designed\nspecifically for it,"},{"time":235442,"text":"and put the things that we can't\npredict on the rooftops."},{"time":238160,"text":"So that was the core idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":239431,"text":"Now, we had to convince the library"},{"time":241149,"text":"that social roles were\nequally important to media,"},{"time":244839,"text":"in order to get them to accept this."},{"time":246642,"text":"What you're seeing here is actually\ntheir program on the left."},{"time":249666,"text":"That's as it was given to us\nin all of its clarity and glory."},{"time":253727,"text":"Our first operation was to re-digest it\nback to them, show it to them and say,"},{"time":258039,"text":"\"You know what? We haven't touched it,"},{"time":260000,"text":"but only one-third of your own program\nis dedicated to media and books."},{"time":263411,"text":"Two-thirds of it is already dedicated --"},{"time":265384,"text":"that's the white band below,\nthe thing you said isn't important --"},{"time":268519,"text":"is already dedicated to social functions.\""},{"time":270552,"text":"So once we had presented\nthat back to them,"},{"time":272757,"text":"they agreed that this sort\nof core concept could work."},{"time":275352,"text":"We got the right to go back\nto first principles --"},{"time":277730,"text":"that's the third diagram."},{"time":278964,"text":"We recombined everything."},{"time":280194,"text":"And then we started making new decisions."}]},{"cues":[{"time":282176,"text":"What you're seeing on the right\nis the design of the library,"},{"time":285073,"text":"specifically in terms of square footage."},{"time":287018,"text":"On the left of that diagram, here,\nyou'll see a series of five platforms --"},{"time":292000,"text":"sort of combs, collective programs."},{"time":294000,"text":"And on the right are the more\nindeterminate spaces;"},{"time":296429,"text":"things like reading rooms,"},{"time":297704,"text":"whose evolution in 20, 30, 40 years\nwe can't predict."},{"time":300413,"text":"So that literally was the design\nof the building."},{"time":302746,"text":"They signed it, and to their chagrin,"},{"time":304905,"text":"we came back a week later,\nand we presented them this."},{"time":308000,"text":"And as you can see, it is literally\nthe diagram on the right."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310921,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":311946,"text":"We just sized -- no, really,\nI mean that, literally."},{"time":314400,"text":"The things on the left-hand side\nof the diagram,"},{"time":316786,"text":"those are the boxes."},{"time":318000,"text":"We sized them into five compartments.\nThey're super-efficient."},{"time":320953,"text":"We had a very low budget to work with."},{"time":322849,"text":"We pushed them around on the site"},{"time":324453,"text":"to make very literal\ncontextual relationships."},{"time":326690,"text":"The reading room\nshould be able to see the water."},{"time":329027,"text":"The main entrance should have\na public plaza in front of it"},{"time":331832,"text":"to abide by the zoning code, and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":334397,"text":"So, you see the five platforms,\nthose are the boxes."},{"time":336874,"text":"within each one, a very discrete\nthing is happening."},{"time":339327,"text":"The area in between\nis sort of an urban continuum,"},{"time":341698,"text":"these things that we can't predict\ntheir evolution to the same degree."},{"time":345490,"text":"To give you some sense\nof the power of this idea,"},{"time":348000,"text":"the biggest block\nis what we call the book spiral."},{"time":351000,"text":"It's literally built\nin a very inexpensive way --"},{"time":353358,"text":"it is a parking garage for books."},{"time":356000,"text":"It just so happens to be on the 6th\nthrough 10th floors of the building,"},{"time":359511,"text":"but that is not necessarily\nan expensive approach."},{"time":362810,"text":"And it allows us to organize\nthe entire Dewey Decimal System"},{"time":365660,"text":"on one continuous run; no matter how it\ngrows or contracts within the building,"},{"time":369555,"text":"it will always have its clarity\nto end the sort of trail of tears"},{"time":374000,"text":"that we've all experienced\nin public libraries."}]},{"cues":[{"time":376753,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":378000,"text":"And so this was the final operation,"},{"time":379755,"text":"which was to take these blocks\nas they were all pushed off kilter,"},{"time":382900,"text":"and to hold onto them with a skin."},{"time":385000,"text":"That skin serves double duty,\nagain, for economics."},{"time":388000,"text":"One, it is the lateral stability\nfor the entire building;"},{"time":391000,"text":"it's a structural element."},{"time":392286,"text":"But its dimensions were designed\nnot only for structure,"},{"time":394937,"text":"but also for holding on\nevery piece of glass."},{"time":397212,"text":"The glass was then --\nI'll use the word impregnated --"},{"time":400000,"text":"but it had a layer of metal\nthat was called \"stretched metal.\""},{"time":403436,"text":"That metal acts as a microlouver,"},{"time":405298,"text":"so from the exterior of the building,\nthe sun sees it as totally opaque,"},{"time":408703,"text":"but from the interior,\nit's entirely transparent."}]},{"cues":[{"time":411401,"text":"So now I'm going to take you\non a tour of the building."},{"time":414871,"text":"Let me see if I can find it."},{"time":416269,"text":"For anyone who gets\nmotion sickness, I apologize."},{"time":420233,"text":"So, this is the building."},{"time":424029,"text":"And I think what's important is,\nwhen we first unveiled the building,"},{"time":427910,"text":"the public saw it as being\ntotally about our whim and ego."},{"time":432000,"text":"And it was defended,\nbelieve it or not, by the librarians."},{"time":434866,"text":"They said, \"Look,\nwe don't know what it is,"},{"time":436914,"text":"but we know it's everything\nthat we need it to be,"},{"time":439303,"text":"based on the observations\nthat we've done about the program.\""},{"time":445085,"text":"This is going into one of the entries."},{"time":447093,"text":"So, it's an unusual building\nfor a public library, obviously."}]},{"cues":[{"time":454000,"text":"So now we're going\ninto what we call the living room."},{"time":457625,"text":"This is actually a program\nthat we invented with the library."},{"time":460521,"text":"It was recognizing that public libraries"},{"time":462462,"text":"are the last vestige of public free space."},{"time":465271,"text":"There are plenty of shopping malls\nthat allow you to get out of the rain"},{"time":468723,"text":"in downtown Seattle,"},{"time":469903,"text":"but there are not so many free places"},{"time":472854,"text":"that allow you to get out of the rain."},{"time":474699,"text":"So this was an unprogrammed area where\npeople could pretty much do anything,"},{"time":478309,"text":"including eat, yell,\nplay chess and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":480442,"text":"Now we're moving up into what we call\nthe mixing chamber."},{"time":484472,"text":"That was the main\ntechnology area in the building."},{"time":487424,"text":"You'll have to tell me\nif I'm going too fast for you."},{"time":494201,"text":"And now up."},{"time":500566,"text":"This is actually the place\nthat we put into the building"},{"time":503219,"text":"so I could propose\nto my wife, right there."}]},{"cues":[{"time":505276,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":508000,"text":"She said yes."}]},{"cues":[{"time":509183,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":512593,"text":"I'm running out of time,\nso I'm actually going to stop."},{"time":515198,"text":"I can show this to you later."},{"time":517000,"text":"But let's see if I can very quickly\nget into the book spiral,"},{"time":520307,"text":"because I think it's,\nas I said, the most --"},{"time":522395,"text":"this is the main reading room --\nthe most unique part of the building."},{"time":526768,"text":"You dizzy yet?"},{"time":529141,"text":"Ok, so here, this is the book spiral."},{"time":536395,"text":"So, it's very indiscernible,"},{"time":538352,"text":"but it's actually\na continuous stair-stepping."},{"time":541877,"text":"It allows you to, on one city block,"},{"time":543893,"text":"go up one full floor,\nso that it's on a continuum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":551491,"text":"Ok, now I'm going to go back,\nand I'm going to hit a second project."},{"time":555000,"text":"I'm going to go very,\nvery quickly through this."},{"time":557287,"text":"Now this is the Dallas Theater."},{"time":558991,"text":"It was an unusual client for us,\nbecause they came to us and they said,"},{"time":562363,"text":"\"We need you to do a new building."},{"time":564093,"text":"We've been working\nin a temporary space for 30 years,"},{"time":567543,"text":"but because of that temporary space,"},{"time":569290,"text":"we've become an infamous theater company."},{"time":572177,"text":"Theater is really focused in New York,\nChicago and Seattle,"},{"time":575162,"text":"with the exception\nof the Dallas Theater Company.\""},{"time":578283,"text":"And the very fact that they worked\nin a provisional space"},{"time":581003,"text":"meant that for Beckett,\nthey could blow out a wall;"},{"time":583470,"text":"they could do \"Cherry Orchard\" and blow\na hole through the floor, and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":587236,"text":"So it was a very daunting task\nfor us to do a brand-new building"},{"time":590292,"text":"that could be a pristine building,"},{"time":592370,"text":"but keep this kind of experimental nature."},{"time":594413,"text":"And the second is,"},{"time":595635,"text":"they were what we call\na multi-form theater,"},{"time":598537,"text":"they do different kinds\nof performances in repertory."},{"time":601167,"text":"So they in the morning\nwill do something in arena,"},{"time":604000,"text":"then they'll do something\nin proscenium and so forth."},{"time":606517,"text":"And so they needed to be able\nto quickly transform"},{"time":608890,"text":"between different theater organizations,"},{"time":610840,"text":"and for operational budget reasons,"},{"time":612549,"text":"this actually no longer\nhappens in pretty much"},{"time":614736,"text":"any multi-form theater\nin the United States,"},{"time":617000,"text":"so we needed to figure out\na way to overcome that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":619499,"text":"So our thought was to literally\nput the theater on its head:"},{"time":622346,"text":"to take those things\nthat were previously defined"},{"time":624680,"text":"as front-of-house and back-of-house"},{"time":626379,"text":"and stack them above house\nand below house,"},{"time":628411,"text":"and to create what we called\na theater machine."},{"time":630634,"text":"We invest the money\nin the operation of the building."},{"time":633141,"text":"It's almost as though the building\ncould be placed anywhere,"},{"time":635987,"text":"wherever you place it,"},{"time":637163,"text":"the area under it is charged\nfor theatrical performances."},{"time":639917,"text":"And it allowed us to go back\nto first principles,"},{"time":642263,"text":"and redefine fly tower, acoustic\nenclosure, light enclosure and so forth."},{"time":645869,"text":"And at the push of a button,"},{"time":647363,"text":"it allows the artistic director\nto move between proscenium, thrust,"},{"time":651014,"text":"and in fact, arena\nand traverse and flat floor,"},{"time":654829,"text":"in a very quick transfiguration."}]},{"cues":[{"time":657248,"text":"So in fact, using\noperational budget, we can --"},{"time":660694,"text":"sorry, capital cost --\nwe can actually achieve"},{"time":662910,"text":"what was no longer achievable\nin operational cost."},{"time":665898,"text":"And that means that the artistic director"},{"time":667875,"text":"now has a palette that he or she\ncan choose from,"},{"time":670264,"text":"between a series of forms\nand a series of processions,"},{"time":673786,"text":"because that enclosure around the theater\nthat is normally trapped"},{"time":676934,"text":"with front-of-house and back-of-house\nspaces has been liberated."},{"time":680000,"text":"So an artistic director has the ability\nto have a performance"},{"time":683293,"text":"that enters in a Wagnerian procession,"},{"time":685432,"text":"shows the first act in thrust,"},{"time":687791,"text":"the intermission in a Greek procession,"},{"time":691000,"text":"second act in arena, and so forth."}]},{"cues":[{"time":693254,"text":"So I'm going to show you\nwhat this actually means."},{"time":695629,"text":"This is the theater up close."},{"time":697421,"text":"Any portion around the theater\nactually can be opened discretely."},{"time":702515,"text":"The light enclosure can be lifted\nseparate to the acoustic enclosure,"},{"time":706437,"text":"so you can do Beckett\nwith Dallas as the backdrop."},{"time":710146,"text":"Portions can be opened,"},{"time":711335,"text":"so you can now actually have motorcycles\ndrive directly into the performance,"},{"time":715002,"text":"or you can even just have\nan open-air performance,"},{"time":717428,"text":"or for intermissions."},{"time":719094,"text":"The balconies all move to go\nbetween those configurations,"},{"time":721851,"text":"but they also disappear."},{"time":723517,"text":"The proscenium line can also disappear."},{"time":726129,"text":"You can bring enormous objects in,"},{"time":727994,"text":"so in fact, the Dallas Theater Company --"},{"time":730009,"text":"their first show will be a play\nabout Charles Lindbergh,"},{"time":732684,"text":"and they'll want to bring in\na real aircraft."},{"time":735000,"text":"And then it also provides them,\nin the off-season,"},{"time":737635,"text":"the ability to actually rent out\ntheir space for entirely different things."},{"time":744000,"text":"This is it from a distance."},{"time":748921,"text":"Open up entire portions\nfor different kinds of events."},{"time":751933,"text":"And at night."},{"time":755092,"text":"Again, remove the light enclosure;\nkeep the acoustic enclosure."},{"time":759676,"text":"This is a monster truck show."}]},{"cues":[{"time":761578,"text":"I'm going to show now the last project."},{"time":763493,"text":"This also is an unusual client."},{"time":765000,"text":"They inverted the whole idea\nof development."},{"time":767497,"text":"They came to us and they said --\nunlike normal developers --"},{"time":770348,"text":"they said, \"We want to start out"},{"time":771909,"text":"by providing a contemporary\nart museum in Louisville."},{"time":774682,"text":"That's our main goal.\""},{"time":775910,"text":"And so instead of being a developer\nthat sees an opportunity to make money,"},{"time":779529,"text":"they saw an ability to be\na catalyst in their downtown."},{"time":782574,"text":"And the fact that they wanted to support\nthe contemporary art museum"},{"time":786178,"text":"actually built their pro forma,"},{"time":787759,"text":"so they worked in reverse."},{"time":789431,"text":"And that pro forma led us"},{"time":791000,"text":"to a mixed-use building\nthat was very large,"},{"time":794000,"text":"in order to support\ntheir aspirations of the art,"},{"time":796328,"text":"but it also opened up opportunities\nfor the art itself"},{"time":798899,"text":"to collaborate, interact\nwith commercial spaces"},{"time":801143,"text":"that actually artists more\nand more want to work within."},{"time":804356,"text":"And it also charged us\nwith thinking about how to have"},{"time":807405,"text":"something that was both a single building"},{"time":809393,"text":"and a credible sort of sub-building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":812000,"text":"So this is Louisville's skyline,"},{"time":814567,"text":"and I'm going to take\nyou through the various constraints"},{"time":817271,"text":"that led to the project."},{"time":818488,"text":"First: the physical constraints."},{"time":820051,"text":"We actually had to operate\non three discrete sites,"},{"time":822476,"text":"all of them well smaller\nthan the size of the building."},{"time":825381,"text":"We had to operate next to the new\nMuhammad Ali Center, and respect it."},{"time":829088,"text":"We had to operate\nwithin the 100-year floodplain."},{"time":831410,"text":"Now, this area floods\nthree to four times a year,"},{"time":833749,"text":"and there's a levee behind our site,"},{"time":835510,"text":"similar to the ones\nthat broke in New Orleans."},{"time":838687,"text":"Had to operate behind the I-64 corridor,"},{"time":842913,"text":"a street that cuts through the middle\nof these separate sites."},{"time":845853,"text":"So we're starting to build a sort of\nnightmare of constraints in a bathtub."},{"time":850443,"text":"Underneath the bathtub\nare the city's main power lines."},{"time":854699,"text":"And there is a pedestrian corridor\nthat they wanted to add,"},{"time":857524,"text":"that would link a series\nof cultural buildings,"},{"time":860498,"text":"and a view corridor --\nbecause this is the historic district --"},{"time":863488,"text":"that they didn't want to obstruct\nwith a new building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866060,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":867124,"text":"And now we're going to add\n1.1 million square feet."},{"time":870125,"text":"And if we did the traditional thing,\nthat 1.1 million square feet --"},{"time":873364,"text":"these are the different programs --"},{"time":875060,"text":"the traditional thing would be to identify\nthe public elements, place them on sites,"},{"time":879048,"text":"and now we'd have a really\nterrible situation:"},{"time":881247,"text":"a public thing in the middle\nof a bathtub that floods."},{"time":885000,"text":"And then we would size\nall the other elements --"},{"time":887621,"text":"the different commercial elements:"},{"time":889300,"text":"hotel, luxury housing,\noffices and so forth --"},{"time":891467,"text":"and dump it on top."},{"time":892696,"text":"And we would create\nsomething that was unviable."},{"time":895684,"text":"In fact -- and you know this -- this\nis called the Time Warner Building."}]},{"cues":[{"time":899453,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":901151,"text":"So our strategy was very simple."},{"time":903000,"text":"Just lift the entire block,"},{"time":906135,"text":"flip some of the elements over,"},{"time":907794,"text":"reposition them\nso they have appropriate views"},{"time":910628,"text":"and relationships to downtown,"},{"time":912288,"text":"and make circulation connections\nand reroute the road."},{"time":915765,"text":"So that's the basic concept,"},{"time":917316,"text":"and now I'm going to show you\nwhat it leads to."}]},{"cues":[{"time":920916,"text":"Ok, it seems a very formal,\nwillful gesture,"},{"time":923495,"text":"but something derived entirely\nout of the constraints."},{"time":926067,"text":"And again, when we unveiled it,\nthere was a sort of nervousness"},{"time":929072,"text":"that this was about an architect\nmaking a statement,"},{"time":931533,"text":"not an architect who was attempting\nto solve a series of problems."},{"time":935149,"text":"Now, within that center zone, as I said,"},{"time":937467,"text":"we have the ability to mix\na series of things."},{"time":939646,"text":"So here, this is sort of an x-ray --"},{"time":942393,"text":"the towers are totally developer-driven."},{"time":944352,"text":"They told us the dimensions,\nthe sizes and so forth,"},{"time":946826,"text":"and we focused on taking\nall the public components --"},{"time":949347,"text":"the lobbies, the bars --"},{"time":950663,"text":"everything that different commercial\nelements would have,"},{"time":954000,"text":"and combined it in the center,\nin the sort of subway map,"},{"time":957000,"text":"in the transfer zone that would also\ninclude the contemporary art museum."}]},{"cues":[{"time":960742,"text":"So it creates a situation like this,\nwhere you have artists who can operate"},{"time":964831,"text":"within an art space that also has\nan amazing view on the 22nd floor,"},{"time":968733,"text":"but it also has proximity that the curator\ncan either open or close."},{"time":972214,"text":"It allows people\non exercise bicycles to be seen,"},{"time":975444,"text":"or to see the art, and so forth."},{"time":977143,"text":"It also means that if an artist wants\nto invade something like a swimming pool,"},{"time":980887,"text":"they can begin to do their exhibition\nin a swimming pool,"},{"time":983621,"text":"so they're not forced to always\nwork within the confines"},{"time":986282,"text":"of a contemporary gallery space."}]},{"cues":[{"time":987841,"text":"So, how to build this."},{"time":989032,"text":"It's very simple: it's a chair."},{"time":991000,"text":"So, we begin by building the cores."},{"time":994456,"text":"As we're building the cores, we build\nthe contemporary art museum at grade."},{"time":998024,"text":"That allows us to have\nincredible efficiency and cost efficiency."},{"time":1001114,"text":"This is not a high-budget building."},{"time":1002839,"text":"The moment the cores get to mid level,"},{"time":1004712,"text":"we finish the art museum; we put\nall the mechanical equipment in it;"},{"time":1007931,"text":"and then we jack it up into the air."},{"time":1009700,"text":"This is how they build\nreally large aircraft hangars,"},{"time":1012213,"text":"for instance, the ones\nthat they did for the A380."},{"time":1014597,"text":"Finish the cores, finish the meat"},{"time":1016461,"text":"and you get something\nthat looks like this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1018498,"text":"Now I only have about 30 seconds,"},{"time":1020100,"text":"so I want to start an animation,"},{"time":1022022,"text":"and we'll conclude with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1023441,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1024853,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1029000,"text":"Chris asked me to add --"},{"time":1031000,"text":"the theater is under construction,"},{"time":1032800,"text":"and this project will start\nconstruction in about a year,"},{"time":1035548,"text":"and finish in 2010."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1036723,"text":"[identify public elements]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1038009,"text":"[insert public elements at grade]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1039620,"text":"[optimize tower dimensions]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1042412,"text":"[place towers on site]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1044115,"text":"[lift program]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1046418,"text":"[flip!]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1048221,"text":"[optimize program adjacencies]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1049833,"text":"[connect to context]"}]},{"cues":[{"time":1051534,"text":"[redirect 7th street]"}]}]}